  <text name="characterHelp" >
    <page>
      <p>[Unit Screen]</p>
      <p>Use this screen to pick up and drop items, wear armor, and select a weapon. You can also view statistics
         about the current unit.</p>
    </page>
    <page image="helpImage4">
      <p>[Inventory]</p>
      <p>
        What the unit is carrying. The top row is in use: the currently worn armor and currently carried
        weapon. You can tap to drop an item, or drag to organize items.</p>
      <p>
        For weapons, the total rounds is displayed below the name. For clips, the number of rounds in the clip is displayed.
      </p>
    </page>

    <page image="helpImage5">
      <p>[Items on the Ground]</p>
      <p>
       The top row is tabs to select groups. Terran Weapons, Alien Weapons, Armor/Shields,
       and Miscellaneous items. Tap to select a tab. Tap an item to pick it up.
      </p>
      <p>
        The number of items available is displayed beneath the item name.
      </p>
    </page>

    <page>
      <p>[Stats and Numbers]</p>
      <p> For the number inclined, the lower right buttons show unit stat info.</p>
      <p> 'Inv' is the default inventory screen. 'Stats' shows the unit statistics. 'Comp' compares weapons carried and on the ground, 
          with buttons to select range.</p>
    </page>
  </text>

  <texture filename="helpImage4.png" width="128" height="128"/>
